Many senators are considering running for governor after Nyeri Governor Nderitu Gachagua s failed impeachment,Kieni MP Kanini Kega has said.Addressing the press at Solio Settlement Scheme in Nyeri town on Thursday, he said the senators now think governors cannot be impeached, even if MCAs recommend their sacking. The law needs to be amended so senators are barred from running for governor, Kega said.He said the Senate has failed in its oversight mandate. at is why the majority of senators are contemplating running for governor, Kega said.